      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The babies kick us off. WASABI BARBIE (4) resumes here but the form she showed in her first preparation was good enough for a race of this calibre. Tuned up for this with a recent trial win and can run a big race while fresh. BARBARIAN KING (2) shed the maiden tag over this track and trip last time out and will have derived some confidence from that victory. Looms as the main danger. COAL SEAM (1) got the maiden out of the way at Mackay on debut before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Top-three aspirations with Wiggins on board. DUB STEPPING (3) is one from one over this sprint trip and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. In the mix. MISSILE BABY (7) is facing the starter for the first time but has shown ability at the trials and any market confidence must be noted.",
